{
  "stem": "12053.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They stayed a whole year in Portugal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It took them a year to process their papers to get them to England, which was a miracle in itself.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Eleanor Rathbone, the late Eleanor Rathbone, MP, she pulled-- she put a legislation through Parliament, letting people, or children under 16, if they have close family in neutral countries-- I mean, you can count them on the fingers of two hands the people who, who it, you know, it was good for-- my parents came into that category.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were allowed to come into England, which they did at the end of 1943, 1943, at the very end.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was before war-- before the war finished.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We could correspond with them in Portugal already.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was marvelous, when we managed to get stamps, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I used to-- that's the one thing I spent whatever money I managed to get, I spent on stamps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we agreed, the three of us agreed, not to mention anything to our parents that we had it so bad.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, they came loaded with presents for them and for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it took just one night for my mother, who slept in my bed-- they made them very welcome.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You see, what had happened, Auntie Vera's mother ran boarding houses in Coventry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's how we got blitzed near the Coventry Cathedral.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they went to evacuate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had a little room in a cottage during The Blitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But those people-- it wasn't their fault.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was the people's fault.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They said they don't want any so-and-so Germans-- they called us the Germans-- in their cottage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they-- we begged to be left behind in the air raid shelter that was still in Coventry.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they were ashamed of the neighbors.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I can understand it.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
